    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_02_19_page01.jpg"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#North-Audley-Street-1_ENK"/>1 north Audley S<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.
                        <date when="1841-02-19">Feb<hi rend="superscript">y</hi>. 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1841</date></dateline>
                    <salute>
                        Dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MurrM1">Miss Murray</persName>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    I am sorry <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MurrJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Murray</persName><lb/>
                    is unwell - I had just<lb/>
                    lain down as is my<lb/>
                    Wont after dinner To sleep<lb/>
                    When your messenger<lb/>
                    came -<unclear>And</unclear> now but half<lb/>
                    awake I write<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    I send 2 or 3 little Tales<lb/>
                    That you may judge of the<lb/>
                    size - There is one other<lb/>
                    Which I have not to send<lb/>
                    but you may judge by<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_02_19_page02.jpg"/>
                    the size of those I send<lb/>
                    what another added<lb/>
                    to them would make -<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    I am gratified by your<lb/>
                    polite assurance that<lb/>
                    you think it an honor<lb/>
                    instead of a trouble to<lb/>
                    write to me - <unclear>even</unclear> on<lb/>
                    business -<lb/>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    I am<lb/>
                    Dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MurrM1">Miss Murray</persName><lb/>
                    Yours sincerely<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MurrJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Murray</persName> will have<lb/>
                        the goodness to return<lb/>
                        The little books as they<lb/>
                        <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1841_02_19_page03.jpg"/>
                        are my <choice><orig>sisters</orig><reg>sister's</reg></choice><lb/>
                        Has <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MurrJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Murray</persName><lb/>
                        yet, the new <choice><orig>Ed<hi rend="superscript">n</hi></orig><reg>Edition</reg></choice> <choice><orig>embellish<lb/>
                                ed</orig><reg>embellished</reg></choice> of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ1"><choice><orig>Lockharts</orig><reg>Lockhart's</reg></choice></persName> <title ref="./Workography.xml#Ancie2">Spanish<lb/>
                        Ballads</title> &amp; could he<lb/>
                        lend them to us<lb/>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
           </div>
        </body>
        <back> </back>
